main event: Two small moon-shaped objects with a white glow were observed in Klamath Falls, Oregon on July 8, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were reported to zig-zag in motion,Observation lasted for 10 seconds before the objects disappeared,Objects were first seen as one and then split into two,Control tower observers were unable to spot the objects,The report concluded that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: Mr. & Mrs. from Klamath Falls, Oregon
